data.name: VSMEF001_MessageFormat
data.value: A property with an [ImportAttribute] must define a setter so the export can be set on the property.
data.comment: {Locked="[ImportAttribute]"} The attribute name in brackets should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF001_Title
data.value: Importing property must have setter

data.name: VSMEF002_MessageFormat
data.value: The type "{0}" contains a mix of attributes from MEFv1 and MEFv2. Consolidate to just one variety of attributes.
data.comment: {Locked="MEFv1"} {Locked="MEFv2"} The framework version names should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF002_Title
data.value: Avoid mixing MEF attribute varieties
data.comment: {Locked="MEF"} The framework name should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF003_MessageFormat
data.value: The type "{0}" does not implement the exported type "{1}". This may be an authoring mistake.

data.name: VSMEF003_Title
data.value: Exported type not implemented by exporting class

data.name: VSMEF004_MessageFormat
data.value: The type "{0}" defines exports but has non-default constructors that are not annotated with [ImportingConstructor]. Add a parameterless constructor, or annotate a constructor with [ImportingConstructor].
data.comment: {Locked="[ImportingConstructor]"} The attribute name in brackets should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF004_Title
data.value: Exported type missing importing constructor

data.name: VSMEF005_MessageFormat
data.value: The type "{0}" has multiple constructors annotated with [ImportingConstructor]. Only one constructor should be marked as importing.
data.comment: {Locked="[ImportingConstructor]"} The attribute name in brackets should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF005_Title
data.value: Multiple importing constructors

data.name: VSMEF006_AllowDefaultWithoutNullable_MessageFormat
data.value: The import "{0}" has AllowDefault = true but is not nullable. Consider making the type nullable or removing AllowDefault.
data.comment: {Locked="AllowDefault"} {Locked="true"} The property name and value should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF006_NullableWithoutAllowDefault_MessageFormat
data.value: The import "{0}" is nullable but does not have AllowDefault = true. Consider adding AllowDefault = true or making the type non-nullable (and either add a 'required' modifier or an '= null!' initializer).
data.comment: {Locked="AllowDefault"} {Locked="true"} {Locked="required"} {Locked="= null!"} The property name, value, and C# keywords/syntax should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF006_Title
data.value: Import nullability and AllowDefault mismatch
data.comment: {Locked="AllowDefault"} The property name should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF007_MessageFormat
data.value: The type "{0}" imports the same contract "{1}" multiple times. Each contract should only be imported once per type.

data.name: VSMEF007_Title
data.value: Duplicate import contract

data.name: VSMEF004_CodeFix_AddImportingConstructorAttribute
data.value: Add [ImportingConstructor] attribute
data.comment: {Locked="[ImportingConstructor]"} The attribute name in brackets should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF004_CodeFix_AddParameterlessConstructor
data.value: Add parameterless constructor

data.name: VSMEF004_CodeFix_AddPartNotDiscoverableAttribute
data.value: Add [PartNotDiscoverable] attribute
data.comment: {Locked="[PartNotDiscoverable]"} The attribute name in brackets should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF006_CodeFix_AddAllowDefault
data.value: Add AllowDefault = true
data.comment: {Locked="AllowDefault"} {Locked="true"} The property name and value should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF006_CodeFix_MakeTypeNonNullable
data.value: Make type non-nullable

data.name: VSMEF006_CodeFix_MakeTypeNullable
data.value: Make type nullable

data.name: VSMEF006_CodeFix_RemoveAllowDefault
data.value: Remove AllowDefault = true
data.comment: {Locked="AllowDefault"} {Locked="true"} The property name and value should not be localized.

data.name: VSMEF008_MessageFormat
data.value: The contract type "{0}" is not assignable to the member type "{1}". The import may fail at runtime.

data.name: VSMEF008_Title
data.value: Import contract type not assignable to member type

data.name: VSMEF009_Title
data.value: ImportMany on non-collection type

data.name: VSMEF009_NonCollection_MessageFormat
data.value: The type "{0}" is not a valid collection type for ImportMany. {1}

data.name: VSMEF009_NotInitialized_MessageFormat
data.value: The property "{0}" has no setter and may not be initialized. {1}

data.name: VSMEF009_ArrayWithoutSetter_MessageFormat
data.value: The property "{0}" is an array without a setter. Arrays cannot be pre-initialized for ImportMany because they don't support Add().

data.name: VSMEF009_LazyWrappingCollection_Detail
data.value: Lazy<T> wrapping a collection is not valid for ImportMany. Use a collection of Lazy<T> instead (e.g., IEnumerable<Lazy<T>>).

data.name: VSMEF009_NotCollectionType_Detail
data.value: The type must be a collection type such as T[], IEnumerable<T>, List<T>, or a type implementing ICollection<T>.

data.name: VSMEF009_MustImplementICollection_Detail
data.value: The type must implement ICollection<T> to support pre-initialization.

data.name: VSMEF009_AddInitializer_Detail
data.value: Add a property initializer (e.g., = new List<T>();) or initialize the property in all constructors.

data.name: VSMEF010_MessageFormat
data.value: The collection type "{0}" is not supported for ImportMany on constructor parameter "{1}". Use T[] or IEnumerable<T> instead.

data.name: VSMEF010_Title
data.value: ImportMany with unsupported collection type in constructor

data.name: VSMEF011_CodeFix_RemoveImportKeepImportMany
data.value: Remove [Import] attribute (keep [ImportMany] for collection)

data.name: VSMEF011_CodeFix_RemoveImportManyKeepImport
data.value: Remove [ImportMany] attribute (keep [Import] for single value)

data.name: VSMEF011_MessageFormat
data.value: The member "{0}" has both [Import] and [ImportMany] attributes. These attributes are mutually exclusive.

data.name: VSMEF011_Title
data.value: Both Import and ImportMany applied to same member

data.name: VSMEF012_CodeFix_MigrateToMefV2
data.value: Migrate to System.Composition.{0}

data.name: VSMEF012_Title
data.value: Disallowed MEF attribute version

data.name: VSMEF012_V1Disallowed_MessageFormat
data.value: MEFv1 attribute "{0}" is not allowed. Use the MEFv2 equivalent from System.Composition.

data.name: VSMEF012_V2Disallowed_MessageFormat
data.value: MEFv2 attribute "{0}" is not allowed. Use the MEFv1 equivalent from System.ComponentModel.Composition.
